  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations in South Carolina for FY2026 to date total $7.3B across 13,264 awards, with an average award size of $554K. Obligations are down 11.8% year over year. Fiscal-year totals show a rise from $6.7B in FY21 to peaks of $10.1B in FY23 and $10.6B in FY24, followed by declines to $8.3B in FY25 and $7.3B in FY26. The Department of Energy accounts for the largest share of FY2026 to date obligations at $4.5B, followed by the Department of Defense at $1.4B. Major vendors include SAVANNAH RIVER NUCLEAR SOLUTIONS LLC at $3.3B and SAVANNAH RIVER MISSION COMPLETION, LLC at $812M. Facilities Support Services is the largest industry by obligations at $3.5B, with Remediation Services at $826M and Commercial and Institutional Building Construction at $545M. These figures are contract obligations and represent fiscal year to date totals; current-year totals are partial. The concentration of spending in a small number of agencies, vendors, and industries is visible in the FY2026 to date distribution.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How have federal obligations trended recently in South Carolina?",
        "body": "Obligations increased from $6.7B in FY21 to $10.6B in FY24 before falling to $8.3B in FY25 and $7.3B in FY26. Overall obligations for FY2026 to date are down 11.8% year over year. The FY2026 to date total of $7.3B reflects partial fiscal-year obligations."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies, vendors, and industries dominate FY2026 to date obligations?",
        "body": "The Department of Energy leads with $4.5B in obligations, and the Department of Defense follows with $1.4B. SAVANNAH RIVER NUCLEAR SOLUTIONS LLC is the largest vendor at $3.3B, and Facilities Support Services is the top industry at $3.5B. Other notable vendors and industries include SAVANNAH RIVER MISSION COMPLETION, LLC at $812M, Remediation Services at $826M, and Commercial and Institutional Building Construction at $545M."
      }
    ]
  },
